2 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
3 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
4 Article – Public Safety
5 14–110.5.
6 (a) (1) In this section the following words have the meanings indicated.
7 (2) “Fund” means the State Disaster Recovery Fund.
8 (3) “Local Disaster Declaration” means a formal request for State disaster
9 relief and recovery assistance made as a result of an emergency by the senior elected official
10 through the local organization for emergency management.
11 (f) (1) The Governor may include in the annual budget bill an appropriation
12 to the Fund.
13 (2) The Fund shall consist of:
14 (i) money appropriated in the State budget to the Fund;
15 (ii) MONEY TRANSFERRED TO THE FUND FROM THE
16 CATASTROPHIC EVENT ACCOUNT IN ACCORDANCE WITH § 7–324 OF THE STATE
17 FINANCE AND PROCUREMENT ARTICLE;
18 (III) repayments of principal and interest from loans made from the
19 Fund;
20 [(iii)] (IV) reimbursements from the federal government or other
21 legal entities for disaster recovery assistance expenditures made from the Fund;
22 [(iv)] (V) interest earnings of the Fund; and
23 [(v)] (VI) any other money from any other source accepted for the
24 benefit of the Fund.
25 Article – State Finance and Procurement
26 7–324.
